SIMPLE: re-enter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Re-enter
<hw>Re-en"ter</hw></mhw> <pr>(r?*?n"t?r)</pr>,
<pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To enter again; <as>as, You cannot
<ex>re-enter</ex> the country with this visa</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Engraving)</fld> <def>To cut deeper, as engraved
lines on a plate of metal, when the engraving has not been deep enough,
or the plate has become worn in printing.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Computers)</fld> <def>To put (data) into a document
or form on a computer again; -- usually to correct an erroneous entry;
<as>as, the password was incorrect, and had to be
<ex>reentered</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Reenter</ent>⟦br⟧
